WEBVTT

01:29.190 --> 01:31.070
For as much as it hath pleased.

01:31.150 --> 01:33.780
Almighty God of His great mercy

01:33.860 --> 01:36.580
to take onto Himself the soul...

01:36.660 --> 01:39.870
of our dear sister
here departed.

01:39.950 --> 01:42.910
We therefore commit her body
to the ground...

01:42.990 --> 01:46.750
earth to earth, ashes to ashes,

01:46.840 --> 01:50.760
dust to dust,
in sure and certain hope

01:50.840 --> 01:53.510
of the resurrection
to eternal life...

01:53.590 --> 01:56.260
through our Lord Jesus Christ,

01:56.340 --> 01:58.720
who shall change our vile body,

01:58.800 --> 02:01.980
that it may be like
unto his glorious body,

02:02.060 --> 02:04.480
according to the mighty working,

02:04.560 --> 02:09.729
whereby he is able to subdue
all things to Himself.

02:15.820 --> 02:17.360
Rest in peace.

02:40.470 --> 02:44.020
- Amber, get in the car.
- I am not getting in the car!

02:44.100 --> 02:45.680
Amber, do you have
to do this today?

02:45.770 --> 02:48.860
- No, I'm not getting in! No!
- Get in the car, please.

02:48.940 --> 02:51.230
- Amber, get in the car.
- Whatever.

03:28.400 --> 03:31.270
Henry Gangon's studio.

03:37.110 --> 03:39.160
- Ah, yeah.
- Henry, it's Josephine.

03:39.240 --> 03:42.200
Okay. One second, one second.
One more.

03:42.280 --> 03:44.870
Jesus Christ!
Okay, hang on.

03:44.950 --> 03:47.040
Josephine.

03:50.790 --> 03:52.750
Hey, Josephine.

03:52.840 --> 03:55.500
Hi, Henry.

03:55.590 --> 03:57.590
Yeah, I should've
come with you.

03:57.670 --> 03:58.670
I'm alright.

03:58.720 --> 04:02.680
Uh, I... I'll meet you in Paris.

04:02.760 --> 04:07.310
I just have to go to
the reading of the will tomorrow

04:07.390 --> 04:10.140
and, um,
take care of things here

04:10.230 --> 04:13.110
once I know what's what.

04:13.190 --> 04:14.210
Look, if this takes
more than a week,

04:14.230 --> 04:16.690
I'm comin' up there, okay?

04:16.779 --> 04:18.649
You've been looking after me
for 23 years

04:18.740 --> 04:21.820
you're more than an assistant,
you're my best friend.

04:21.910 --> 04:24.830
That's very kind.

04:24.910 --> 04:28.540
- Josephine, I do have to go.
- Okay.

04:28.620 --> 04:30.710
I will call you tomorrow, okay?

04:39.590 --> 04:41.970
Josephine Malone.
Terry Baginski.

04:42.050 --> 04:44.140
I'm stepping in for Arnie today.

04:46.760 --> 04:49.770
Mr. Spear is late,
which isn't a surprise.

04:49.850 --> 04:51.850
Who is Mr. Spear?

04:51.940 --> 04:54.270
He's the other person mentioned
in your grandmother's will.

05:09.960 --> 05:12.670
Mr. Spear has arrived.

05:12.750 --> 05:13.750
- Terry?
- Oh...

05:13.790 --> 05:15.380
I'm sorry. A-are you alright?

05:15.460 --> 05:17.670
My apologies. Yes.

05:17.750 --> 05:20.920
- You're Josie.
- Josephine.

05:21.010 --> 05:25.100
Malone. Uh...
Lydia's, uh, granddaughter.

05:25.180 --> 05:27.260
I know.

05:35.270 --> 05:37.190
"I, Lydia Josephine Malone,

05:37.270 --> 05:38.940
"being of very sound mind

05:39.020 --> 05:41.070
"and knowingly questionable body

05:41.150 --> 05:43.660
"do hereby bequeath
all my worldly possessions

05:43.740 --> 05:47.030
"to my granddaughter,
Josephine Diana Malone.

05:47.120 --> 05:50.100
"This includes Lavender House
and my investment portfolio.

05:51.080 --> 05:55.710
"I bequeath everything
to Josephine but $150,000.

05:55.790 --> 05:58.090
"This will be provided
to Mr. James Marcum Spear

05:58.170 --> 06:00.260
"in order that he put it
in a trust.

06:00.340 --> 06:03.510
"Fifty thousand each
for Connor Marcum Spear,

06:03.590 --> 06:07.470
"Amber Jolan Spear
and Ethan James Spear.

06:07.550 --> 06:09.890
"And last,
my most prized possession,

06:09.970 --> 06:12.770
"the thing I treasure above
anything else in this world,

06:12.850 --> 06:15.730
"my granddaughter,
Josephine Diana Malone,

06:15.810 --> 06:18.650
I hereby bequeath
to James Marcum Spear."

06:18.730 --> 06:20.520
- What?
- What?

06:20.610 --> 06:22.820
"Jake, Josie is quite awkward
and I don't mean simply

06:22.900 --> 06:24.650
"that she is a complete klutz.

06:24.740 --> 06:26.740
"She doesn't know
how to enjoy herself.

06:26.820 --> 06:28.740
"But if you find your way
to coax it out of her,

06:28.820 --> 06:30.090
"she gives off
the sweetest light

06:30.120 --> 06:31.910
"that will ever shine on you.

06:31.990 --> 06:35.790
"I'm trusting you, my Jake,
to take good care of her.

06:35.870 --> 06:39.090
"These are my wishes
and I will them to be done.

06:39.170 --> 06:41.130
"If they're not, I'll know

06:41.210 --> 06:43.090
"and it'll make me very upset

06:43.170 --> 06:45.010
"I know neither of you
want that.

06:45.090 --> 06:48.800
Now, be blissfully happy,
my Josie and my Jake."

06:52.100 --> 06:54.770
Did Lydie just leave me
you in her will?

06:54.850 --> 06:59.270
Obviously, the bequeathal
of a human being isn't binding.

06:59.360 --> 07:03.030
Copies of Mrs. Malone's official
last will and testament.

07:03.110 --> 07:04.940
There's also contact information

07:05.030 --> 07:06.530
for Stone Incorporated.

07:06.610 --> 07:09.620
They're interested
in purchasing Lavender House.

07:18.620 --> 07:19.920
Although gran
didn't mention you,

07:20.000 --> 07:21.630
it's clear she held you
and your children

07:21.710 --> 07:22.750
in very high regard.

07:22.840 --> 07:25.420
So, it was a pleasure
to meet you.

07:25.510 --> 07:27.590
Goodbye.

07:28.260 --> 07:30.850
Wait. Hey, hey, hang on.
Josie, wait...

07:30.930 --> 07:33.220
- Mr. Spear, not to be rude...
- Jake.

07:33.310 --> 07:34.930
My name's Jake.

07:35.020 --> 07:36.660
Look, something big
just happened in here.

07:36.680 --> 07:38.730
Indeed, and if you're concerned,

07:38.810 --> 07:40.150
I'll take issue with the gifts

07:40.230 --> 07:41.860
my grandmother bestowed
on your children.

07:41.940 --> 07:43.580
- Please don't be.
- No, it's not what I'm saying.

07:43.610 --> 07:45.650
I'm talkin'
about the other gift, Josie.

07:45.740 --> 07:47.780
Nobody calls me Josie.

07:47.860 --> 07:49.950
Lydie did.

07:51.820 --> 07:53.580
Tonight, we need to have dinner.

07:53.660 --> 07:54.970
I'm afraid dinner
is out of the question.

07:55.050 --> 07:56.260
I see that you're trying
to pretend like

07:56.290 --> 07:59.330
that didn't just happen,
but it did happen.

07:59.420 --> 08:02.340
I mean, the least we could do is
get to know each other, right?

08:02.420 --> 08:04.590
Don't we owe her that respect?

08:04.670 --> 08:07.090
I mean, look, if I'm a dick,
then that's it.

08:07.170 --> 08:08.570
But I'm not gonna be a dick
to Lydie's girl,

08:08.590 --> 08:10.260
because that woman
meant a lot to me,

08:10.340 --> 08:12.970
and to my kids.

08:13.050 --> 08:14.560
When and where?

08:14.640 --> 08:16.980
Lobster Market, 6:30.

08:17.060 --> 08:19.140
I'll see you there.

08:21.310 --> 08:23.320
It's nice to finally meet you,
Josie.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.480
Uh, Josephine.

08:40.460 --> 08:42.789
May I join you?

08:42.880 --> 08:46.500
I wouldn't mind, but there's
a man in my life who would.

08:48.380 --> 08:50.470
Well, if I were that man,

08:50.550 --> 08:53.470
I would hate for you
to dine alone.

08:53.550 --> 08:55.470
Well, he's busy this evening

08:55.560 --> 08:58.350
and I had a craving
for lobster bisque, so...

09:02.770 --> 09:04.820
If you had a craving
for anything,

09:04.900 --> 09:07.070
I would make sure you got it.

09:07.150 --> 09:08.740
Actually, Jake knows
I'm quite capable

09:08.820 --> 09:11.530
of getting what I want
on my own.

09:11.610 --> 09:13.240
Jake?

09:13.320 --> 09:14.620
Jake Spear.

09:16.780 --> 09:19.080
What, you used to dance for him?

09:19.160 --> 09:20.370
What?

09:20.460 --> 09:22.370
Class piece.

09:22.460 --> 09:24.420
Looks like Jake's
finally learned to trade up.

09:24.500 --> 09:26.170
I beg your pardon?

09:26.250 --> 09:28.920
If you're lookin' to be
the fourth Mrs. Jake Spear,

09:29.000 --> 09:30.970
let me just tell you,
he might make a fortune

09:31.050 --> 09:33.430
from that strip club,

09:33.510 --> 09:35.430
but the Truck goes through women
like water.

10:22.560 --> 10:24.100
What the hell?

10:24.190 --> 10:27.480
You know, it's been a long time
since someone stood me up.

10:27.560 --> 10:29.250
If you had any idea
what it took to get Amber

10:29.270 --> 10:30.590
to babysit her brother
last night.

10:30.650 --> 10:32.610
How did you get in here?

10:32.690 --> 10:34.900
I have keys.
All the kids have keys.

10:34.990 --> 10:36.010
Ethan comes here after school.

10:36.030 --> 10:37.030
Well, I will have to ask

10:37.070 --> 10:39.120
for those to be returned.

10:39.200 --> 10:40.490
Seriously?

10:40.580 --> 10:41.800
Did my grandmother know
you own a strip club?

10:41.830 --> 10:43.620
Yeah, she did.

10:43.700 --> 10:46.250
Seeing as she lent me
the money to buy it.

10:46.330 --> 10:48.460
So your business

10:48.540 --> 10:51.050
is to objectify women?

10:51.130 --> 10:53.720
I see. So I'm an asshole?

10:53.800 --> 10:55.300
Alright. I didn't know that.

10:55.380 --> 10:56.800
Seeing as my least talented girl

10:56.880 --> 10:58.450
makes at least 500 a night,
on a slow night.

10:58.470 --> 11:00.470
I might be just a teensy bit
judgmental

11:00.560 --> 11:03.060
if she told me she was loaning
a man money to buy a strip club.

11:03.140 --> 11:05.020
A man who's been married
three times.

11:05.100 --> 11:06.810
Oh!

11:06.900 --> 11:09.610
Okay. You've been
askin' around about me.

11:09.690 --> 11:10.900
Lydie told me you were classy,

11:10.980 --> 11:12.400
didn't tell me
you were judgmental.

11:12.480 --> 11:14.900
You don't know me.

11:14.990 --> 11:17.070
I might know you
better than you think.

11:28.540 --> 11:30.630
Hm...

11:31.460 --> 11:33.670
Why didn't you tell me
about him, gran?

11:44.520 --> 11:46.560
Excuse me, I'm Boston Stone.

11:46.640 --> 11:48.230
CEO of Stone Incorporated.

11:48.310 --> 11:49.620
I don't wanna bother you,
except to ask

11:49.650 --> 11:51.110
if you'd like
to have lunch with me

11:51.190 --> 11:53.110
to discuss your plans
for the Lavender House.

11:53.190 --> 11:57.570
Um, my grandmother passed away
five days ago, and, um...

11:57.650 --> 11:59.240
There are a lot of things
on my mind,

11:59.320 --> 12:01.490
but not one of them
is discussing

12:01.580 --> 12:03.200
my plans for Lavender House.

12:03.280 --> 12:04.950
Of course.
I'm sorry for your loss.

12:05.040 --> 12:07.200
If you change your mind...

12:49.290 --> 12:51.370
Hm...

14:07.240 --> 14:10.790
- What'll it be?
- A club soda.

14:10.870 --> 14:14.960
And can someone tell Mr. Spear
that I'm here to see him?

14:43.110 --> 14:46.030
Mr. Spear is unavailable.
Can I give him a message?

14:46.110 --> 14:48.200
No, but thank you.

14:57.790 --> 15:00.840
Mr. Spear...
Uh, Jake...

15:00.920 --> 15:03.420
This is Josephine Malone
calling.

15:03.510 --> 15:06.840
Uh, I just wanted
the opportunity to apologize,

15:06.930 --> 15:11.720
and also, I just wanted the
chance to talk to you about...

15:11.810 --> 15:13.890
other things.

15:15.100 --> 15:17.190
Dammit!

15:30.370 --> 15:33.290
- Hello.
- Hello.

15:33.370 --> 15:34.930
I gotta tell you,
you really classed up the joint

15:34.960 --> 15:36.120
seeing you in there.

15:36.210 --> 15:38.040
- Oh, you saw me?
- Yeah, of course I did.

15:38.120 --> 15:40.100
We got cameras everywhere
just in case some drunk asshole

15:40.130 --> 15:42.210
gets out of line,
gotta take care of him.

15:44.090 --> 15:46.380
You, uh...
Somethin' you wanna say to me?

15:48.220 --> 15:49.800
I-I don't know
if you have consultants

15:49.890 --> 15:52.220
for this kinda thing,
but the brunette is gorgeous.

15:52.300 --> 15:55.020
Uh, with her skin tone, a deeper
auburn will suit her much better

15:55.100 --> 15:57.060
she'd make a fabulous redhead.

15:57.140 --> 15:59.100
And the blonde, she's so cute,
she just needs

15:59.190 --> 16:01.650
a manicure
and a keratin treatment.

16:01.730 --> 16:04.400
Okay. Ha-ha-ha!

16:04.480 --> 16:06.990
Oh, yeah. Lydie was right.
Adorable.

16:07.070 --> 16:10.120
- Sorry?
- Uh, nothin'. Um...

16:10.200 --> 16:12.580
Is that, is that the message
you had for me?

16:12.660 --> 16:16.120
I'd like for you to come
to dinner at Lavender House

16:16.200 --> 16:17.710
tomorrow night. Um...

16:17.790 --> 16:20.330
Gran clearly wanted us
to get to know each other

16:20.420 --> 16:23.460
and we should do that.

16:23.540 --> 16:25.840
Yeah.

16:27.260 --> 16:29.510
I'm just not sure
how she wanted us

16:29.590 --> 16:31.510
to get to know each other.

16:31.600 --> 16:34.310
Look, don't worry about it,
alright? You're not my type.

16:39.810 --> 16:43.980
I mean, I don't think
I was your type either.

16:44.060 --> 16:49.990
I-I don't understand
what gran wanted for you and me.

16:50.070 --> 16:53.280
I don't know,
but, I mean, maybe she...

16:53.370 --> 16:55.450
wanted you to know
you had a friend

16:55.540 --> 16:57.540
and still had at least
one person who cared.

16:57.620 --> 17:01.920
Well, that makes no sense.
She knew I had Henry.

17:02.000 --> 17:05.089
Yeah, I don't care what excuses
you make for that guy.

17:05.170 --> 17:07.410
He should've been with you
at your grandmother's funeral.

17:07.460 --> 17:08.480
Instead of letting you
stand there

17:08.510 --> 17:10.589
crying behind your shades alone.

17:13.260 --> 17:17.970
Well, you promise you're not
gonna ghost on me tomorrow,

17:18.060 --> 17:20.480
and I'll show,
but, uh, I gotta tell you

17:20.560 --> 17:23.900
I gotta bring Ethan with me.

17:23.980 --> 17:26.440
Alright, then.
Goodnight, Jake.

17:26.520 --> 17:28.610
Goodnight, Josephine.

17:29.690 --> 17:33.030
Hey, y-you can call me Josie.

17:34.490 --> 17:36.580
Goodnight, Josie.

17:45.750 --> 17:48.000
Um...

17:56.220 --> 17:57.350
- Hello.
- Hey.

17:57.430 --> 17:58.720
So, Amber got herself grounded

17:58.810 --> 18:00.430
two seconds
before we left the house,

18:00.520 --> 18:02.040
so if you don't have enough
food, I can order a pizza.

18:02.060 --> 18:04.860
- Or something.
- Oh, no, I have enough food.

18:04.940 --> 18:06.900
Hi, Amber, it's a pleasure
to meet you.

18:06.980 --> 18:09.070
Whatever.

18:10.030 --> 18:12.110
- Hello, Ethan.
- Hi.

18:15.660 --> 18:17.370
- Josie.
- Come on in.

18:17.450 --> 18:19.540
Okay.

18:24.040 --> 18:26.840
- It smells boss.
- Mm.

18:26.920 --> 18:28.590
Ooh. Yeah, it does.

18:28.670 --> 18:30.920
It smells like meat.
I'm a vegetarian.

18:31.010 --> 18:33.970
Ah, right.
She decided that this morning.

18:34.050 --> 18:35.800
Killing animals for food
is disgusting.

18:35.890 --> 18:39.850
How about killin' daughters
for bein' a pain in my ass?

18:39.930 --> 18:41.350
Crap! What is that?

18:41.430 --> 18:44.020
It's pavlova.
We're having it for dessert.

18:44.100 --> 18:47.900
I don't eat dessert.
My ass is already fat enough.

18:47.980 --> 18:50.070
Get me a beer, will ya, bud?

18:53.360 --> 18:55.200
Um, everything is done.

18:55.280 --> 18:57.950
I wasn't sure if he needed to
get home early to do homework...

18:58.030 --> 19:01.080
No, no. The, uh,
homework's in the truck.

19:01.160 --> 19:03.250
Alright. Dinner's ready.

19:10.130 --> 19:13.550
Rosemary meatloaf
with romesco sauce.

19:13.630 --> 19:15.840
Oh!

19:15.930 --> 19:18.140
- Don't you like meatloaf?
- No. Yeah. No, I do.

19:18.220 --> 19:19.930
I thought we were gonna
have to choke down

19:20.010 --> 19:22.350
coq au vin or something.

19:22.430 --> 19:24.100
Do you want some, Amber?

19:24.180 --> 19:26.240
I heard being vegetarian
is a good way to lose weight.

19:26.270 --> 19:27.870
I don't know why you'd be
worried about that.

19:27.900 --> 19:30.150
You have a perfect body.

19:30.230 --> 19:33.940
I don't know if my grandmother
told you, but I work in fashion.

19:34.030 --> 19:37.990
I hope you don't mind my saying,
but you're exceptionally pretty.

19:38.070 --> 19:41.120
Go a little less heavy
on the make-up.

19:41.200 --> 19:44.540
Jean Michel Duchamp taught me
how to do make-up.

19:44.620 --> 19:45.100
I have both of his books.

19:46.080 --> 19:49.170
My boss Henry shot the one
with the models.

19:49.250 --> 19:51.800
Oh, my God!
How did I not know that?

19:51.880 --> 19:53.150
Lydie told me that
you worked for Henry Gangon,

19:53.170 --> 19:54.460
I should've known that.

19:54.550 --> 19:56.020
If you want,
I could take your picture

19:56.050 --> 19:57.800
and ask him to share
some pointers.

19:57.880 --> 20:01.220
Are you freaking serious?
Oh, my freaking God.

20:01.300 --> 20:02.660
Dad, you have to lift the ban
on my cell phone

20:02.680 --> 20:04.600
so I can tell Taylor and Taylor
about this.

20:04.680 --> 20:06.850
- Who's Taylor and Taylor?
- Her best friends.

20:06.940 --> 20:08.310
Yeah, you can tell them
tomorrow.

20:08.400 --> 20:09.730
- Please, dad.
- Mm-hm.

20:09.810 --> 20:11.730
The easiest way to get
what you want

20:11.820 --> 20:13.520
is by listening to your father.

20:13.610 --> 20:14.980
Yeah, listen to your father

20:15.070 --> 20:17.240
when he's totally unreasonable
about Noah.

20:17.320 --> 20:18.990
- Who's Noah?
- My boyfriend.

20:19.070 --> 20:21.580
He wants to take me to a concert
and dad refuses to let me go.

20:21.660 --> 20:25.870
She used the F-word
like a bazillion times.

20:25.950 --> 20:27.550
Well, you're a beautiful girl

20:27.620 --> 20:30.420
and Noah could be
a paragon of virtue.

20:30.500 --> 20:33.710
But if your dad loves you,
it's his job to be cautious.

20:33.800 --> 20:37.170
If he didn't care,
that's when you should be upset.

20:40.680 --> 20:42.760
That's what Lydie would say.

20:45.560 --> 20:48.060
- To Lydie!
- Hey, to Lydie.

20:48.140 --> 20:50.230
To Lydie.

20:58.990 --> 21:00.320
Well, dinner was great, huh?

21:00.400 --> 21:02.490
Oh, I'm glad you liked it.

21:03.820 --> 21:06.660
Boston Stone came by.

21:06.740 --> 21:08.500
He what?

21:08.580 --> 21:10.750
He's interested in buying
Lavender House.

21:10.830 --> 21:14.340
Yeah, but Lydie told him
to go jump in the Atlantic.

21:14.420 --> 21:16.840
And what did you say to Stone?

21:16.920 --> 21:20.300
I told him I wasn't prepared
to discuss it.

21:20.380 --> 21:22.800
Are you gonna get prepared?

21:22.890 --> 21:25.300
Nope.

21:25.390 --> 21:26.970
So you're keeping
Lavender House?

21:27.060 --> 21:30.060
Lydie said the only person
who loves Lavender House

21:30.140 --> 21:32.440
more than her is Josie,

21:32.520 --> 21:34.860
and that she'd never let it out
of the family.

21:37.400 --> 21:39.610
The only person who loves
Lavender House more than gran

21:39.690 --> 21:44.700
is me, and I'd never let it out
of the family, so...

21:44.780 --> 21:46.950
Yeah, I'm-I'm keeping the house.

21:47.040 --> 21:49.290
Yes!

21:49.370 --> 21:52.540
Hey, you go pour yourself
some wine, I got this.

22:08.810 --> 22:11.810
- It was lovely to meet you.
- Same.

22:11.890 --> 22:15.480
The food was freaking awesome!

22:17.980 --> 22:19.360
- It was a good night.
- Thanks.

22:19.440 --> 22:22.030
Thank you. Um...

22:22.110 --> 22:24.950
Tell you what, tomorrow,
