tomorrow night.

48:35.770 --> 48:38.190
Are you and Jake an item?

48:38.270 --> 48:40.270
We're just friends.

48:40.360 --> 48:43.530
How about we do dinner,
Sunday night?

48:43.610 --> 48:46.660
I'd like that, Micky.

48:46.740 --> 48:49.570
But I should go. Ethan and I
are making cream puffs.

48:49.660 --> 48:51.740
Eth, you got cream puffs
to make.

48:56.920 --> 49:00.500
- See you Sunday.
- Bye.

49:00.580 --> 49:03.550
Hey, Josie, you going to dad
and Micky's fight Saturday?

49:03.630 --> 49:06.050
- Yeah.
- Awesome!

49:06.130 --> 49:09.220
I usually go, but Combat Raptor
comes out tomorrow

49:09.300 --> 49:11.640
and I'm going to Josh's, and
we're all going to the movies,

49:11.720 --> 49:14.640
and then I'm sleepin' over,
I can't freaking wait!

49:14.720 --> 49:16.640
How do you know
if you're gonna like it?

49:16.730 --> 49:18.230
Uh, Josie,

49:18.310 --> 49:21.770
it's Combat Raptor!

49:21.860 --> 49:24.320
Are Connor and Amber
going to your dad's fight?

49:24.400 --> 49:25.650
Amber? No way.

49:25.740 --> 49:27.900
She'll be on a date with Noah.

49:27.990 --> 49:29.610
Connor normally always goes,

49:29.700 --> 49:32.080
but he's scrapin' off
all his girlfriends.

49:32.160 --> 49:33.970
So, he'll probably be breaking
some chick's heart

49:33.990 --> 49:35.660
Saturday night.

49:35.740 --> 49:38.100
Connor is breaking up
with his girlfriends?

49:39.080 --> 49:42.000
- Dad laid down the law.
- Uh-huh.

49:42.080 --> 49:43.210
- You wanna drive?
- Sure.

49:43.300 --> 49:45.380
What? Get in the car!

50:04.480 --> 50:06.820
Here.

50:06.900 --> 50:09.180
You know, Lydie knitted this
for me three Christmases ago.

50:09.240 --> 50:12.870
Aw! Thanks.

50:12.950 --> 50:14.950
I'm gonna get some cocoa,
do you want some?

50:15.040 --> 50:17.120
Yeah. It's right over there.

50:28.380 --> 50:30.010
- Hi, you're Josie.
- I am and you are?

50:30.090 --> 50:32.470
I'm Taylor,
I'm Amber's bestest bestie.

50:32.550 --> 50:35.180
Well, one of them.
She's spoken of you, like, lots.

50:35.260 --> 50:36.850
Your outfit is very chic.

50:36.930 --> 50:39.230
And you wear it well,
it just needs a fedora.

50:39.310 --> 50:40.850
I know, right?
But I'll be lucky

50:40.940 --> 50:42.460
if I don't get tripped,
pushed, or run down

50:42.480 --> 50:44.500
before the night is through,
destroying these trousers.

50:44.520 --> 50:46.110
Well, small-minded fools
are everywhere,

50:46.190 --> 50:48.190
and those who have the courage
to be who they are

50:48.280 --> 50:50.110
often have to suffer them.

50:50.200 --> 50:53.530
You totally looked through Amber
like she wasn't even there.

50:53.620 --> 50:56.950
- You done with her yet?
- Amber Spear is a total tease.

50:57.040 --> 50:58.370
And her dad's a pain in my ass.

50:58.450 --> 51:00.410
Won't let her go
to the Bounce concert.

51:00.500 --> 51:03.420
She's hot, but if Amber likes
her cherry that much,

51:03.500 --> 51:05.880
she can keep it.

51:05.960 --> 51:08.880
- Are you Noah?
- Yeah, I'm Noah.

51:08.960 --> 51:10.510
Well, Noah, you should know

51:10.590 --> 51:12.720
that Amber won't be going
to the concert with you

51:12.800 --> 51:15.470
because she and the Taylors
are going with me.

51:15.550 --> 51:17.510
I'm a friend of Lavon's
and he doesn't like

51:17.600 --> 51:19.270
a lot of people backstage.

51:19.350 --> 51:21.180
And Amber wanted to give her
backstage passes

51:21.270 --> 51:22.980
to her best besties.

51:23.060 --> 51:25.690
Oh, and as for your idea
that Amber's a tease,

51:25.770 --> 51:28.190
she isn't,
she's just not that into you.

51:28.280 --> 51:29.960
So, please, you totally look
through Amber.

51:29.980 --> 51:32.530
It'll save you some frustration
and maybe heartbreak

51:32.610 --> 51:34.280
when she finds out
how shallow you are

51:34.360 --> 51:35.360
and cuts you loose.

51:35.450 --> 51:37.200
Holy shit.

51:37.280 --> 51:38.660
Oh, and one final thing,

51:38.740 --> 51:40.140
badmouthing a woman
when everyone can hear

51:40.160 --> 51:41.410
is just bad manners.

51:41.500 --> 51:43.750
Says nothing about the woman
and everything

51:43.830 --> 51:46.840
about your own character.

51:46.920 --> 51:48.420
You may wanna move forward,
Taylor.

51:48.500 --> 51:50.500
- We're losing the line.
- That was epic.

51:50.590 --> 51:54.050
Well, we gotta hurry up
and text Amber.

51:54.130 --> 51:56.680
I so totally told you, Amber.
He's completely up his own ass.

51:56.760 --> 51:58.410
He is, girlfriend,
he is so not worth

51:58.430 --> 51:59.490
putting up with all of this.

51:59.510 --> 52:00.810
I think that's true, I think

52:00.890 --> 52:02.220
I maybe even said that to him

52:02.310 --> 52:04.390
and probably fibbed a bit.

52:06.350 --> 52:07.940
You fibbed?

52:08.020 --> 52:11.570
I told him I was taking you
and the Taylors to Bounce.

52:11.650 --> 52:13.960
But first, you guys need to get
permission from your parents

52:13.990 --> 52:15.700
and I need to discuss it
with your father.

52:15.780 --> 52:17.910
And second, you need to tread
very carefully tonight.

52:17.990 --> 52:20.990
I have no idea how he's gonna
react to my little talk.

52:21.080 --> 52:23.080
He called me a tease?

52:23.160 --> 52:25.750
- He acted like he liked me.
- I mean, he probably does.

52:25.830 --> 52:28.670
He just has to show
a certain face to his friends.

52:28.750 --> 52:32.590
But, Josie, I've liked him
since, like, forever.

52:32.670 --> 52:35.300
I know, i-it's just...

52:35.380 --> 52:37.550
He may not live up to what you
thought he would be.

52:37.640 --> 52:40.100
- He was totally a douche.
- He's always been a douche.

52:40.180 --> 52:42.020
It's completely inappropriate
for me to call

52:42.100 --> 52:43.580
a teenage boy a douche,
but you're right,

52:43.600 --> 52:47.350
he was a total douche.

52:47.440 --> 52:49.400
Ugh! I hate you!

52:49.480 --> 52:53.360
- No, no. Mia!
- Go away.

52:53.440 --> 52:55.320
Uh-oh! He's cutting Mia off,

52:55.400 --> 52:57.490
and she's not takin' it well.

53:03.580 --> 53:05.660
- Whoo!
- Nice.

53:09.460 --> 53:11.750
Oh, I have a few things
to tell you.

53:11.840 --> 53:13.460
Uh, with your permission
I'd like to take

53:13.550 --> 53:16.130
Amber and the Taylors
to see Bounce in Boston.

53:16.220 --> 53:17.940
Oh, and Amber and Noah,
if they were ever together,

53:17.970 --> 53:20.970
they're broken up, I maybe
partially responsible for that.

53:21.050 --> 53:22.780
It's likely there'll be some
teenager-girl moods

53:22.810 --> 53:24.430
in your house
for the foreseeable future

53:24.520 --> 53:27.560
and I'd like to apologize
for that in advance.

53:27.640 --> 53:31.310
Jesus, slick,
how long were you gone?

53:31.400 --> 53:33.480
Hey. Ellie.

53:35.070 --> 53:37.150
We need to talk.

53:40.070 --> 53:42.160
Amber.

53:46.330 --> 53:48.330
That's my girl.

53:48.420 --> 53:49.830
You take good care of her.

53:49.920 --> 53:53.170
I think I get more out of it
than she does.

53:53.250 --> 53:56.130
Oh, then you think wrong, slick.

53:56.210 --> 53:58.300
Come on.

54:05.520 --> 54:06.770
Thanks.

54:06.850 --> 54:08.810
- This is Jake.
- Hey.

54:08.890 --> 54:10.900
How are Connor and Amber?

54:10.980 --> 54:13.320
Hey! Uh, well...

54:13.400 --> 54:14.900
Amber's doing little better
than Con,

54:14.980 --> 54:16.000
Connor had
kind of a rough night.

54:16.030 --> 54:18.240
He, uh, broke up with Mia.

54:18.320 --> 54:21.950
But then, uh, his final choice,
Ellie, dumped him

54:22.030 --> 54:24.240
when, uh, he told her
that she had made the cut.

54:24.330 --> 54:28.120
Oh. I'm not sure "made the cut"
was the right choice of words.

54:28.200 --> 54:30.330
Yeah, you think?

54:30.420 --> 54:32.170
Are you working out?

54:32.250 --> 54:34.290
Yeah, somethin' like that.

54:34.380 --> 54:35.710
I'll call you later.

54:35.800 --> 54:37.880
Alright, slick.

54:53.520 --> 54:55.770
- Josephine.
- Hi!

54:55.860 --> 54:57.070
How are you doing?

54:57.150 --> 55:00.320
Jet-lagged.
Just got to Paris.

55:00.400 --> 55:02.570
I-I need some help,
I need some advice.

55:02.660 --> 55:04.200
I'm going
to a boxing match tonight

55:04.280 --> 55:06.870
and I don't know what to wear.

55:06.950 --> 55:08.740
Why are you going to a fight,
Josephine?

55:08.830 --> 55:11.790
I've been asked by the fighters.

55:11.870 --> 55:14.330
Plural?

55:14.420 --> 55:16.710
That's my Josephine girl there.

55:16.800 --> 55:18.480
Been there a couple weeks
and she's setting

55:18.500 --> 55:21.260
Maine on fire with her ice.

55:21.340 --> 55:23.430
You smoke everything you put on,

55:23.510 --> 55:25.260
but you gonna have to
trick yourself out.

55:25.340 --> 55:28.310
Man see a girl sittin' ringside
and shit's hot,

55:28.390 --> 55:30.390
and she's lookin' all ice cold,

55:30.480 --> 55:31.810
that might be some ammunition

55:31.890 --> 55:34.020
for him to kick
some serious ass.

55:34.100 --> 55:35.650
Tricked out it is.

55:35.730 --> 55:37.150
How you doin' otherwise?

55:37.230 --> 55:40.650
I have my moments,
but gran had good friends

55:40.740 --> 55:42.650
and they're taking care of me.

55:42.740 --> 55:44.360
Good!

55:44.450 --> 55:46.010
I'mma check my schedule
in the next couple of weeks

55:46.030 --> 55:47.780
and see if I can come
check you out.

55:47.870 --> 55:49.870
- I hope so, I'd love that.
- Alright.

55:49.950 --> 55:51.830
- I'mma talk to you later.
- Bye.

55:51.910 --> 55:53.100
Alright.

56:15.770 --> 56:16.770
Hi.

56:16.810 --> 56:18.900
Josephine Malone.

56:20.900 --> 56:23.900
Here you are.

56:26.410 --> 56:28.490
Thank you.

56:32.830 --> 56:34.920
Right.

56:43.840 --> 56:46.050
- Hey. Oh.
- I'm Alyssa. Junior's woman.

56:46.130 --> 56:47.430
Hi. Josephine.

56:47.510 --> 56:49.760
I know. Jake's woman.

56:49.850 --> 56:52.140
Word gets around.

56:52.220 --> 56:54.180
So, Junior's up next,
he's fighting Micky.

56:54.270 --> 56:56.020
But don't worry
when Micky messes him up.

56:56.100 --> 56:57.480
Nobody beats Mick but Jake.

56:57.560 --> 57:00.020
Then again,
Jake messes everyone up.

57:00.110 --> 57:01.820
I'm sorry?

57:01.900 --> 57:03.150
Junior doesn't care.

57:03.240 --> 57:05.110
He gets to celebrate
after anyway,

57:05.200 --> 57:06.780
win or lose.

57:06.860 --> 57:08.070
You get me?

57:09.990 --> 57:12.740
Nothing better than a fighter
after a fight,

57:12.830 --> 57:17.790
all that aggression, all that
adrenaline still flowing. Mm...

57:17.870 --> 57:19.210
I love fight night.

57:24.590 --> 57:25.900
Let's go. Fight's on. Let's go!

57:29.510 --> 57:31.720
Mess him up, baby!

57:31.800 --> 57:34.850
Go, tiger.

57:34.930 --> 57:38.020
Is this your first fight?
You'll get me, honey.

57:38.100 --> 57:41.060
Get ready for the ride
of your life, girlfriend.

57:42.190 --> 57:43.820
Oh, come on.

57:43.900 --> 57:45.860
Come on, baby. Go, baby!

57:45.940 --> 57:47.150
I love you, Tiger!

57:47.240 --> 57:49.320
I love you, Tiger!

57:53.120 --> 57:55.120
